## 2. External AI Integration

### Claude (Anthropic)

```python
POST https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
Headers:
  x-api-key: <your_key>
  anthropic-version: 2023-06-01
  content-type: application/json
Body:
  {
    "model": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
    "max_tokens": 2048,
    "system": "<system prompt>",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "..."}]
  }
```

### OpenAI / Compatible

```python
POST https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions
Headers:
  Authorization: Bearer <key>
Body:
  {
    "model": "gpt-4o",
    "messages": [
      {"role": "system", "content": "..."},
      {"role": "user",   "content": "..."}
    ]
  }
```

### Ollama (local)

```python
POST http://localhost:11434/api/chat
Body:
  {
    "model": "llama3",
    "messages": [...],
    "stream": false
  }
```

### Dependency Installation

Blender ships its own Python with **no pip packages**.
The add-on bootstraps missing packages on first load:

```python
subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, "-m", "pip", "install", "--user", pkg])
```

Packages are installed to the user site-packages directory
(`~/.local/lib/python3.11/site-packages/` on Linux/macOS,
`%APPDATA%\Python\Python311\site-packages` on Windows).

