## 5. Local LLM vs Cloud API

| | Cloud (Claude/OpenAI) | Local (Ollama/llama.cpp) |
|---|---|---|
| **Quality** | ★★★★★ | ★★★ (depends on model) |
| **Speed** | 2–10 s (network) | 5–60 s (hardware-dependent) |
| **Privacy** | Prompts leave machine | Fully local |
| **Cost** | Per token | Free after hardware |
| **Setup** | API key only | Install + download model (4–70 GB) |
| **Blender blocking** | Thread + timer ✓ | Thread + timer ✓ |
| **Embedding in Blender** | HTTP call only | HTTP to localhost:11434 |

**Verdict:** Embedding an LLM *inside* Blender's process is **not practical**
because Blender's Python cannot load GPU extensions (llama-cpp-python's
CUDA/Metal backends) and the memory footprint would dwarf Blender itself.
Always run the model out-of-process (cloud API or local Ollama/LM Studio
server) and communicate via HTTP.

